verbose_text: Accumulating evidence suggests bufalin could inhibit the proliferation of multiple tumor cell types, including human colon cancer cells (colon, 26-L5), leukemia cells (K562, U937, ML1 and HL-60), hepatocellular carcinoma cells (SMMC-7721 and Bel-7402), prostate cancer cells (LNCaP, DU 145 and PC3), endometrial carcinoma cells (HHUA and HEC-1), and ovarian cancer cells (SK-OV3 and omc-3).
